# XAML is classified as a "data" language by GitHub Linguist, which excludes
# data/prose languages from repo language stats by default (same as JSON,
# YAML...) even though the files are real UI markup, not generated data.
# linguist-detectable alone re-enabled counting but let Linguist's ambiguous-
# extension heuristics decide the label — they predate .NET MAUI's XML
# namespace and fell back to plain "XML". Force the exact language instead.
*.xaml linguist-language=XAML
